âš¡ 3. Interaction Rules (Critical)
3.1 NEVER Use Browser Alerts

Absolutely banned:

alert()

confirm()

prompt()

They feel cheap, break immersion, and ruin the premium look.

3.2 Inline Confirmation Pattern (MANDATORY)

Every user-triggered action follows the same 3-step button lifecycle:

Default

Send Quote

Loading

Sendingâ€¦

Show spinner

Disable button

Tint button slightly

Success

Button turns green (bg-green-600)

Icon: Check

Text changes to â€œSent!â€

150â€“200ms scale animation

Optionally revert after 2â€“3 seconds

This replaces all popups.

Standard code pattern:

const [state, setState] = useState("idle"); 
// idle | loading | success | error

<Button
  disabled={state === "loading"}
  className={cn(
    "transition-all duration-200",
    state === "success" && "bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-600 cursor-default"
  )}
>
  {state === "loading" && <Loader2 className="mr-2 h-4 w-4 animate-spin" />}
  {state === "success" && <Check className="mr-2 h-4 w-4" />}
  {state === "idle" && "Send Quote"}
  {state === "loading" && "Sendingâ€¦"}
  {state === "success" && "Sent!"}
</Button>

3.3 Errors are Inline, Not Popups

Errors appear directly under the button:

Red text

1â€“2 lines max

Clear action: â€œPlease enter a valid email.â€

